<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300745678</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
SCENE I. <attbytes>6Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>BOOK</TY><ID>Z300745678</ID><A1>Adams, C. L. (Charles L.)</A1><T1>Or The Fatal Duel</T1><PBL>Publisher unknown</PBL><Y1>1809</Y1><T2>Literature Online</T2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage r="italic">An apartment in <hi r="roman">Madame de Vineuil's</hi> house. Enter
<hi r="smcap">Madame de Vineuil.</hi></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="1">ALAS! all the living hope that now</pl>
<pl ln="2">remains, is centered in my only and beloved son, if</pl>
<pl ln="3">he should not meet with success in his flattering expectations</pl>
<pl ln="4">I am sure my languishing heart will</pl>
<pl ln="5">break.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r" r="italic">Enter <hi r="smcap">Matilda.</hi></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="6">Oh! ma'am, here is a letter for you, it has</pl>
just come.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="7">A letter, <stage r="italic">(eagerly)</stage> do pray give it</pl>
<pl ln="8">me.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="9">Do ma'am read it, for I fear some unlucky</pl>
<pl ln="10">accident has happened to prevent Charles's</pl>
<pl ln="11">coming.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><stage r="italic"><speaker>Mad. de Vin</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform>. (opens the letter and reads)</stage><p><pl ln="12">Dear</pl>
<pl ln="13">Mother, the flattering prospects and expectations</pl>
<pl ln="14">of my being admitted into partnership with the commercial</pl>
<pl ln="15">house at Nantz, are now accomplished. I</pl>
<pl ln="16">have secured a share in it, and I am now in a condition</pl>
<pl ln="17">to provide for you and my beloved sister. You</pl>
<pl ln="18">may expect me home to&hyphen;morrow.</pl></p>
<p r="smcap" align="r">Charles de Vineuil.</p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="19">To&hyphen;morrow, Oh! dear ma'am, how I long</pl>
<pl ln="20">to see Charles, and Mr Favelle will be so glad to</pl>
<pb n="4">
<pl ln="21">know him. Indeed ma'am I have often heard him</pl>
<pl ln="22">say that Charles was his friend although he did not</pl>
<pl ln="23">know him.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="c" r="italic">Enter <hi r="smcap">Servant.</hi></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Ser.</speaker><fullform>Servant</fullform><p><pl ln="24">Madame, Mr Favelle.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="25">Conduct him in.</pl></p>
<stage>[<hi r="italic">exit</hi> Servant</stage></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="c" r="italic">Enter <hi r="smcap">Favelle.</hi></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="26">Good morning to you ladies.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de V. <hi r="roman">and</hi> Mat.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil, Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="27">Good morning, Sir.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="28">As I passed your door, I perceived the penny&hyphen;</pl>
<pl ln="29">post deliver a letter, I hope no misfortune has interfered</pl>
<pl ln="30">with your son's hopeful prospects.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="31">No sir, I assure you it is quite the reverse,</pl>
<pl ln="32">he has met with success in business, and the</pl>
<pl ln="33">joyful intelligence has tended to remove, in a great</pl>
<pl ln="34">measure, the tumult of my anxiety. The last fond</pl>
<pl ln="35">hope of a mother's wish is now completed by the</pl>
<pl ln="36">good conduct, industry and talents, by which my beloved</pl>
<pl ln="37">offspring is amply merited.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><stage r="italic"><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform> (aside)</stage><p><pl ln="38">Indeed methinks that is the very tone</pl>
<pl ln="39">of adoration, multiplied by the twinkling light of</pl>
<pl ln="40">fortitude. Indeed madam I rejoice at your son's success.</pl>
<pl ln="41">Nothing could give me more satisfaction, than</pl>
<pl ln="42">to receive your approbation to initiate him as my</pl>
<pl ln="43">bosom friend&mdash;But Matilda why is this speechless</pl>
<pl ln="44">sorrow, you are not well perhaps?</pl></p><stage>(<hi r="italic">taking her by the hand</hi>.)</stage></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="45">Sir I've been anticipating about&mdash;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="46">Love, I presume.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="47">No sir, concerning my fortunate brother.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="48">I presume you expect your brother very soon</pl>
<pl ln="49">to see you.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="50">To&hyphen;morrow he has appointed to come.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="51">Indeed! but ladies you must excuse me, as</pl>
<pl ln="52">I have business to transact.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="53">Sir I shall expect you to&hyphen;morrow.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="54">Madame I'll wait on you with pleasure</pl>
<pl ln="55">Good morning ladies.</pl></p></speech></pdiv><stage>[<hi r="italic">exeunt</hi></stage></div3>
<pb n="5">
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300745679</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
SCENE II. <attbytes>3Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>BOOK</TY><ID>Z300745679</ID><A1>Adams, C. L. (Charles L.)</A1><T1>Or The Fatal Duel</T1><PBL>Publisher unknown</PBL><Y1>1809</Y1><T2>Literature Online</T2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage align="c" r="italic">Enter <hi r="smcap">Charles de Vineuil.</hi></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Cha. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Charles de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="1">'Tis surprising indeed, to find no one</pl>
<pl ln="2">yet. Well here I am after a short journey, and a surprising</pl>
<pl ln="3">one I presume to my mother. Ah! here she</pl>
<pl ln="4">comes.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><stage align="c" r="italic">Enter <speaker>Madame de Vineuil.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform></stage>
<p><pl ln="5">My mother!</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="6">My son!</pl></p></speech></pdiv><stage>(<hi r="italic">they embrace</hi>)</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Cha. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Charles de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="7">But why that fretful anguish. Dispel</pl>
<pl ln="8">those antick difficulties, nor doubt, but that the</pl>
<pl ln="9">filial love I've borne for you, still shall retain</pl>
<pl ln="10">the center of my youthful heart. Did you receive</pl>
<pl ln="11">my letter of yesterday.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="12">I did, and viewed it with the greatest</pl>
<pl ln="13">alacrity. But come, relate to me the progress of</pl>
<pl ln="14">your adventures.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Cha. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Charles de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="15">Indeed that would be too tedious to</pl>
<pl ln="16">relate at present.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><stage><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform> (<hi r="italic">without</hi>)</stage><p><pl ln="17">Charles! Charles! oh! where is</pl>
<pl ln="18">he. <stage>(<hi r="italic">running in and embracing him</hi>.)</stage> I hope nothing has</pl>
<pl ln="19">happened since you wrote us the letter.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Cha. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Charles de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="20">Nothing.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="21">Oh! ma'am, if Mr Favelle&wblank;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Cha. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Charles de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="22">Favelle, <stage>(<hi r="italic">turning to his mother</hi>)</stage> is he</pl>
<pl ln="23">not the friend you mentioned in your letter.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="24">Oh! dear yes, he is one of the most friendly</pl>
<pl ln="25">young men. I wish you could but see him.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Cha. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Charles de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="26">Indeed I have always testified an extraordinary</pl>
<pl ln="27">desire to become acquainted with the</pl>
<pl ln="28">friend of your house; but I have no time to spare;</pl>
<pl ln="29">I have business of importance that must be speedily</pl>
<pl ln="30">attended to.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">exeunt.</hi></stage></div3>
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300745680</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
SCENE III. <attbytes>2Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>BOOK</TY><ID>Z300745680</ID><A1>Adams, C. L. (Charles L.)</A1><T1>Or The Fatal Duel</T1><PBL>Publisher unknown</PBL><Y1>1809</Y1><T2>Literature Online</T2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage r="italic">A noise without, Enter <hi r="smcap">Favelle Charles de
Vineuil, Albertus</hi> and <hi r="smcap">Ferdinand.</hi></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Alb.</speaker><fullform>Albertus</fullform><p><pl ln="1">Why do you hesitate, challenge him at once</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="6">
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Cha. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Charles de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="2">Gentlemen, I have been grossly insulted,</pl>
<pl ln="3">and I now declare myself ready to fight.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><stage><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform> (<hi r="italic">moderately</hi>)</stage><p><pl ln="4">&ldquo;If we fight it will be of no advantage</pl>
<pl ln="5">to any body. You assert that I have insulted</pl>
<pl ln="6">you; it is possible that an unguarded word may</pl>
<pl ln="7">have escaped me; but we were both in a passion,</pl>
<pl ln="8">and both, at least, equally in fault.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Ferd.</speaker><fullform>Ferdinand</fullform><p><pl ln="9">&ldquo;Ha! he retracts his words.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Alb.</speaker><fullform>Albertus</fullform><p><pl ln="10">&ldquo;He preaches, he is afraid.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="11">&ldquo;No gentlemen I am not afraid; and as little</pl>
<pl ln="12">as I deem it a disgrace to be fond of life, so little</pl>
<pl ln="13">do I tremble at the thoughts of death. Now gentlemen</pl>
<pl ln="14">we must fight.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Alb.</speaker><fullform>Albertus</fullform><p><pl ln="15">&ldquo;Bravo, bravo.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Ferd.</speaker><fullform>Ferdinand</fullform><p><pl ln="16">&ldquo;To&hyphen;morrow then, at eight o'clock.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Alb.</speaker><fullform>Albertus</fullform><p><pl ln="17">Agreed, at the <hi r="italic">Champs Elysees</hi>. Gentlemen,</pl>
<pl ln="18">all I have to request is, punctuality and honour in</pl>
<pl ln="19">the affair.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>By&hyphen;standers.</speaker><fullform>By&hyphen;standers</fullform><p><pl ln="20">Bravo, bravo.</pl></p></speech></pdiv><stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">exeunt.</hi></stage></div3>
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300745681</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
SCENE IV. <attbytes>2Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>BOOK</TY><ID>Z300745681</ID><A1>Adams, C. L. (Charles L.)</A1><T1>Or The Fatal Duel</T1><PBL>Publisher unknown</PBL><Y1>1809</Y1><T2>Literature Online</T2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage r="italic">Champs Elysees. Front of the stage the ground is
measured for the duelists, behind which is a table. Enter
<hi r="smcap">Favelle.</hi></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="1">Alas! this is the fatal spot.&mdash;&ldquo;Shall I, for a</pl>
<pl ln="2">mere trifle, in order to escape the ridicule of a few</pl>
<pl ln="3">hen&hyphen;hearted coxcombs, run the risk of being killed</pl>
<pl ln="4">myself, or of murdering one who appears to be a</pl>
<pl ln="5">well&hyphen;bred man.&rdquo; If I should perchance murder my</pl>
<pl ln="6">antagonist, what reparation can be made to alleviate</pl>
<pl ln="7">the pangs of my guilty conscience.&mdash;Nay, nay, I will</pl>
<pl ln="8">not fight.</pl></p>
<stage r="italic">Enter <hi r="smcap">Charles De Vineuil, Albertus, Ferdinand</hi>
and seconds, the seconds with pistols.</stage></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Alb.</speaker><fullform>Albertus</fullform><p><pl ln="9">Now gentlemen, are you ready to decide upon</pl>
<pl ln="10">this point of honour.</pl></p>
<stage>(Charles de Vineuil <hi r="italic">seizes one of the pistols and stands at his post, the by&hyphen;standers whisper to each other</hi>.)</stage></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="7">
<pdiv><speech><stage><speaker>Ferd.</speaker><fullform>Ferdinand</fullform> (<hi r="italic">to Alb</hi>.)</stage><p><pl ln="11">Ha! he is afraid, he will not fight</pl></p>
<stage>(<hi r="italic">this rouses Favelle's resentment, he eagerly siezes the
pistol and flies to his post. They fire</hi>, Charles de Vineuil
<hi r="italic">falls</hi>)</stage></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><stage><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform> (<hi r="italic">with a loud shriek throws away his pistol</hi>)</stage>
<p><pl ln="12">Ha! miscreants, villains, why have you brought me</pl>
<pl ln="13">to this.</pl></p>
<stage>(<hi r="italic">he siezes a pistol that remains on the table and attempts to shoot himself, but is prevented by</hi> Albertus)</stage></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Alb.</speaker><fullform>Albertus</fullform><p><pl ln="14">Young man, take my advice, and quit this</pl>
<pl ln="15">fatal spot. I will not leave your antagonist, but try</pl>
<pl ln="16">every possible means for his recovery.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">exit</hi> Eavelle. <hi r="italic">Scene closes</hi></stage></div3>
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300745682</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
SCENE V. <attbytes>5Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>BOOK</TY><ID>Z300745682</ID><A1>Adams, C. L. (Charles L.)</A1><T1>Or The Fatal Duel</T1><PBL>Publisher unknown</PBL><Y1>1809</Y1><T2>Literature Online</T2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage r="italic">Bois de Boulougne. Enter <hi r="smcap">Favelle</hi> disorderly,
<hi r="smcap">Durand</hi> following.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Dur.</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform><p><pl ln="1">&ldquo;God be thanked that I have met you, I may</pl>
<pl ln="2">prevent an accident.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="3">&ldquo;Who speaks to me?&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Dur.</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform><p><pl ln="4">&ldquo;Your friend, who wishes to advise you for</pl>
<pl ln="5">your own good. Young man, listen to reason,</pl>
<pl ln="6">would you fight for such a trifle? Can a person of</pl>
<pl ln="7">such a gentle, generous disposition as you be guilty</pl>
<pl ln="8">of such a folly? Perhaps I can prevent a great misfortune.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="9">&ldquo;Do you think you can?&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Dur.</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform><p><pl ln="10">&ldquo;Perhaps I can; be not carried away by a</pl>
<pl ln="11">false point of honour, and risk not your life so wantonly.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="12">&ldquo;My life? By no means.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Dur.</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform><p><pl ln="13">&ldquo;Well, supposing you to be more dexterous</pl>
<pl ln="14">and more fortunate than your antagonist, supposing</pl>
<pl ln="15">he falls, would you, who deem it a happiness to save</pl>
<pl ln="16">the life of a man, would you wish to kill him? Would</pl>
<pl ln="17">not your soul be forever burdened with the guilt of</pl>
<pl ln="18">murder.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="19">&ldquo;O God! yes.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="8">
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Dur.</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform><p><pl ln="20">&ldquo;Well then, do nor fight, Rather say to</pl>
<pl ln="21">your opponent, I acknowledge that I was in the</pl>
<pl ln="22">wrong.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="23">&ldquo;It is too late!&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Dur.</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform><p><pl ln="24">&ldquo;Not yet&mdash;your antagonist&mdash;&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="25">&ldquo;Is dead&rdquo;&mdash;and I am murderer! (<hi r="italic">swoons</hi>)</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><stage><speaker>Dur,</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform> (<hi r="italic">after a pause</hi>)</stage><p><pl ln="26">Unhappy youth, thy virtue is</pl>
<pl ln="27">at last betrayed by the hard pressure of unfeeling friendship.</pl>
<pl ln="28"><stage>(<hi r="italic">he raises</hi> Favelle <hi r="italic">in his arms</hi>)</stage> Young man, suffer</pl>
<pl ln="29">me to administer to you some consolation.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="30">Oh! the pernicious pangs of guilt that now</pl>
<pl ln="31">o'erwhelm me, drive my tortured soul to madness.&mdash;</pl>
<pl ln="32">But where, where is he, is he not&mdash;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Dur.</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform><p><pl ln="33">Be not too rash young man, &ldquo;but let me</pl>
<pl ln="34">give you to understand that it is necessary to employ</pl>
<pl ln="35">precaution to avoid the consequences of this rencounter.&rdquo;</pl>
<pl ln="36">Therefore I will return alone; and you</pl>
<pl ln="37">must speedily repair to Paris, to the house of Madame</pl>
<pl ln="38">de Vineuil, and keep yourself concealed, till I</pl>
<pl ln="39">shall send you word that you may return without</pl>
<pl ln="40">danger to your own lodgings.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="41">Even as you say; I'll follow your advice.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Dur.</speaker><fullform>Durand</fullform><p><pl ln="42">Let not the tumult of pour sanguine passion</pl>
<pl ln="43">betray your conscience. Heaven lend you prosperous</pl>
<pl ln="44">wings, to help you out of this sad difficulty.</pl>
<pl ln="45">Farewell, but do not hesitate.</pl></p><stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">exeunt.</hi></stage></speech></pdiv></div3>
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300745683</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
SCENE V. <attbytes>3Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>BOOK</TY><ID>Z300745683</ID><A1>Adams, C. L. (Charles L.)</A1><T1>Or The Fatal Duel</T1><PBL>Publisher unknown</PBL><Y1>1809</Y1><T2>Literature Online</T2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage r="italic">An apartment in <hi r="roman">Madame de Vineuil's</hi> house, the
body of <hi r="roman">Charles</hi> extended on a sofa, the weeping mother
embracing the knees of her murdered child. <hi r="roman">Matilda</hi>
leaning over her brother.</stage>
<stage align="c" r="italic">Enter <hi r="smcap">Servant.</hi></stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Ser.</speaker><fullform>Servant</fullform><p><pl ln="1">Mr. Favelle, madame.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="2">Admit him.</pl>
<pl ln="3"><stage r="italic">(exit <hi r="roman">Servant</hi>. As <hi r="roman">Favelle</hi> enter, <hi r="roman">Matilda</hi>, in tears, runs to meet him)</stage> &ldquo;Oh! Mr.</pl>
<pl ln="4">Favelle, my brother! my unfortunate brother is killed!&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pb n="9">
<pdiv><speech><stage><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform> (<hi r="italic">starts back</hi>)</stage><p><pl ln="5">Oh! hellish guilt!</pl></p>
<stage>(<hi r="italic">he attempts to retire, but is prevented by</hi> Matilda)</stage></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="6">&ldquo;Alas! my brother!&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mad. de Vin.</speaker><fullform>Madame de Vineuil</fullform><p><pl ln="7">My son! my son!</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="8">Killed too, for a mere trifle, for a word,</pl>
<pl ln="9">&ldquo;he did not wish to fight; he wanted to make up</pl>
<pl ln="10">the quarrel. He was urged on, ridiculed, and pains</pl>
<pl ln="11">were taken to inflame his resentment.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="12">Alas! then 'twas&mdash;<stage>(<hi r="italic">aside</hi>)</stage> By heaven the</pl>
<pl ln="13">fearful confession trembles upon my lips.</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Mat.</speaker><fullform>Matilda</fullform><p><pl ln="14">&ldquo;He was your friend, though he did not</pl>
<pl ln="15">know you; how he rejoiced at the thoughts of seeing</pl>
<pl ln="16">you.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="17">Oh! hell&hyphen;black conscience. &ldquo;Alas! I am</pl>
<pl ln="18">his murderer.&rdquo;</pl></p></speech></pdiv><stage align="r">[<hi r="italic">exit.</hi></stage></div3>
<div3>
<comhd3><idref>Z300745684</idref><collection>1 2</collection>
SCENE VI. <attbytes>3Kb</attbytes><reflink></reflink><comcitn><TY>BOOK</TY><ID>Z300745684</ID><A1>Adams, C. L. (Charles L.)</A1><T1>Or The Fatal Duel</T1><PBL>Publisher unknown</PBL><Y1>1809</Y1><T2>Literature Online</T2></comcitn></comhd3>
<stage r="italic">An apartment in <hi r="roman">Durand's</hi> house. Enter <hi r="roman">Favelle</hi>,
in confusion, with a vial.</stage>
<pdiv><speech><speaker>Fav.</speaker><fullform>Favelle</fullform><p><pl ln="1">At last I am bereft of even hope&mdash;oh! death,</pl>
<pl ln="2">death, why are thy bounds extenuated. Oh! thou</pl>
<pl ln="3">palatable pleasure of my mind, for many long and</pl>
<pl ln="4">tedious hours have I disdain'd to sleep, waiting the</pl>
<pl ln="5">unexpected arrival of thy power, to obliterate the</pl>
<pl ln="6">remembrance of so foul a deed&mdash;a deed too horrible</pl>
<pl ln="7">to be alleviated.&mdash;To rob a mother of her darling</pl>
<pl ln="8">son! nay, e'en of her protector from the raging tempest</pl>
<pl ln="9">of famine and despair&mdash;oh! excrutiating guilt,</pl>
<pl ln="10">that drives my loathsome soul within the boundaries</pl>
<pl ln="11">of dissimulation. Now may thy faculties prove</pl>
<pl ln="12">fruitful, that I may gain a welcome reception to</pl>
<pl ln="13">the remotest cell of eternal oblivion.&mdash;Come then,</pl>
<pl ln="14">thou delicious cordial, and let me receive thy venomous</pl>
<pl ln="15">pangs as the sacred pleasure of my inmost</pl>
<pl ln="16">soul. <stage>(<hi r="italic">puts the vial to his mouth, a groan is heard</hi>)</stage></pl>
<pl ln="17">Ah! from whence did that proceed! is it to exterminate</pl>
<pl ln="18">my design.&mdash;Methinks I see him there&mdash;ah!</pl>
<pb n="10">
<pl ln="19">'tis he! behold the horrid swell of guilt denounc'd against</pl>
<pl ln="20">me. Why is not the gloomy aspect of that</pl>
<pl ln="21">form radicated within the mouldering earth&mdash;indeed</pl>
<pl ln="22">thou look'st as if thou had'st definitively came to</pl>
<pl ln="23">warn me 'ganst another evil, if not, answer we,</pl>
<pl ln="24">wherefore do I see that gentle form thrice renovated.</pl>
<pl ln="25">&mdash;Nay then, if thou wilt not answer, pardon your</pl>
<pl ln="26">murderer.&mdash;Ah! methought thy lips did more, as if</pl>
<pl ln="27">'twere to denounce my sentence&mdash;forgive me ere I</pl>
<pl ln="28">resign my afflicted soul to hell's sad dwelling&mdash;ah!</pl>
<pl ln="29">he retreats! stay, stay, if you thus slight me, I'll ransack</pl>
<pl ln="30">the whole earth but that I'll find thee&mdash;e'en</pl>
<pl ln="31">then, I'll swear to mock thy gloomy gestures, and</pl>
<pl ln="32">throw destruction's guide within thy path&mdash;nay then,</pl>
<pl ln="33">I'll follow thee, though the thunderbolt of heaven</pl>
<pl ln="34">should crush me to thy mouldering den.</pl></p>
<stage>(<hi r="italic">a flash of lightning, he attempts to run, but falls senseless</hi>)</stage></speech></pdiv></div3>
